<h1>rubik</h1>
<p>
The <b><a href="http://www.rubiks.com/">Rubik's Cube Game</a></b> is a 3D game for Linux written in <a href="http://live.gnome.org/Vala">Vala</a> using the <a href="http://www.clutter-project.org">Clutter</a> framework.
</p>
<p>
Latest version is 1.1. Grab the sources: <a href="$(ROOT)/download/rubik-1.1.tar.gz">rubik-1.1.tar.gz</a>.<br />
Development version at the <a href="https://github.com/lethalman/rubik">git repository</a>.<br />
</p>

<h1>features</h1>
<p>
<ul>
<li>&rarr; game timer and moves count</li>
<li>&rarr; rotate slice cube in a natural manner</li>
<li>&rarr; shuffle the cube</li>
<li>&rarr; save the state of the cube on exit <em>(under $HOME/.rubik)</em></li>
<li>&rarr; rotate the cube in several easy ways</li>
</ul>
</p>

